{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13`, but the preserved work branch appears to contain a viable fix: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3301-library-new-request-com.github.java-json-tools-json-patch-1.13-c5a6e150\n\nThe most likely failing stage was `nativeTest`, not test generation itself. The metrics completed successfully in `stats/com.github.java-json-tools/json-patch/1.13/execution-metrics.json` (`status: success`, 5 iterations, 297 generated LOC), and `stats/com.github.java-json-tools/json-patch/1.13/stats.json` reports `dynamicAccess` as `0/0` with about `88.25%` line coverage. The concrete failure shows up in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-38-54-287972Z.log`: `:nativeTest` failed because `removingMissingPathReportsPatchException()` and `failedTestOperationAbortsPatchAndLeavesInputUnchanged()` expected human-readable messages like `no such path` / `value differs`, but the native image only returned raw keys `jsonPatch.noSuchPath` / `jsonPatch.valueTestFailure`.\n\nThe preserved follow-up logs suggest the missing piece was the resource bundle `com/github/fge/jsonpatch/messages.properties`. That is called out in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13/metadata-fix/codex.log`, and later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-42-16-509677Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-42-37-147407Z.log` show all 9 native tests passing.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `metadata/com.github.java-json-tools/json-patch/1.13/reachability-metadata.json` and `tests/src/com.github.java-json-tools/json-patch/1.13/src/test/java/com_github_java_json_tools/json_patch/Json_patchTest.java`.\n2. Compare the failing `15-38-54` native test log with the later passing `15-42-16` / `15-42-37` logs to confirm the resource-registration fix is the only required change.\n3. If that review checks out, rerun the targeted metadata/test validation for `com.github.java-json-tools:json-patch:1.13` and submit the preserved branch as the fix."}}
